        "from poolparty import (\n",
        "    Pool, \n",
        "    KmerPool,\n",
        "    ListPool,\n",
        "    ShuffledPool,\n",
        "    RandomMutationPool,\n",
        "    KMutationPool,\n",
        "    SubseqPool,\n",
        "    shuffle,\n",
        "    generate_seqs\n",
        ")\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"✓ poolparty imported successfully!\")\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## 1. Basic Pool Operations\n",
        "\n",
        "The `Pool` class is the foundation of poolparty. Let's start with simple operations.\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": 2,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [
        {
          "name": "stdout",
          "output_type": "stream",
          "text": [
            "Pool sequence: ACGT\n",
            "Pool length: 4\n",
            "Number of states: 1\n",
            "Is finite?: True\n"
          ]
        }
      ],
      "source": [
        "# Create a simple pool with a fixed sequence\n",
        "pool1 = Pool(seq=\"ACGT\")\n",
        "print(f\"Pool sequence: {pool1.seq}\")\n",
        "print(f\"Pool length: {len(pool1)}\")\n",
        "print(f\"Number of states: {pool1.num_states}\")\n",
        "print(f\"Is finite?: {pool1.is_sequential_compatible()}\")\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "### Concatenation\n",
        "\n",
        "Pools can be concatenated using the `+` operator:\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": 3,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [
        {
          "name": "stdout",
          "output_type": "stream",
          "text": [
            "Pool + Pool: ACGTTGCA\n",
            "Pool + string + Pool: ACGTNNNNNTGCA\n"
          ]
        }
      ],
      "source": [
        "# Concatenate pools and strings\n",
        "prefix = Pool(seq=\"ACGT\")\n",
        "suffix = Pool(seq=\"TGCA\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# Pool + Pool\n",
        "combined = prefix + suffix\n",
        "print(f\"Pool + Pool: {combined.seq}\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# Pool + string\n",
        "with_adapter = prefix + \"NNNNN\" + suffix\n",
        "print(f\"Pool + string + Pool: {with_adapter.seq}\")\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "### Repetition and Slicing\n",
        "\n",
        "Use `*` for repetition and `[]` for slicing:\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": 4,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [
        {
          "name": "stdout",
          "output_type": "stream",
          "text": [
            "Repeated 5 times: ACGACGACGACGACG\n",
            "Sliced [2:8]: GTACGT\n"
          ]
        }
      ],
      "source": [
        "# Repetition\n",
        "motif = Pool(seq=\"ACG\")\n",
        "repeated = motif * 5\n",
        "print(f\"Repeated 5 times: {repeated.seq}\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# Slicing\n",
        "long_seq = Pool(seq=\"ACGTACGTACGT\")\n",
        "sliced = long_seq[2:8]\n",
        "print(f\"Sliced [2:8]: {sliced.seq}\")\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## 2. KmerPool: Generate K-mers\n",
        "\n",
        "`KmerPool` generates k-mer sequences of a specified length from an alphabet. It has a **finite** number of states equal to `len(alphabet)^length`.\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": 5,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [
        {
          "name": "stdout",
          "output_type": "stream",
          "text": [
            "KmerPool: AA\n",
            "Number of states: 4 (2^2 = 4)\n",
            "Is finite?: True\n",
            "\n",
            "All 2-mers from 'AB': ['AA', 'AB', 'BA', 'BB']\n"
          ]
        }
      ],
      "source": [
        "# Create a KmerPool for all 2-mers from 'AB'\n",
        "dimers = KmerPool(length=2, alphabet='AB')\n",
        "print(f\"KmerPool: {dimers}\")\n",
        "print(f\"Number of states: {dimers.num_states} (2^2 = 4)\")\n",
        "print(f\"Is finite?: {dimers.is_sequential_compatible()}\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# Generate all k-mers\n",
        "all_dimers = generate_seqs(dimers, combinatorially_complete_pools=[dimers], num_complete_iterations=1)\n",
        "print(f\"\\nAll 2-mers from 'AB': {all_dimers}\")\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": 6,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [
        {
          "name": "stdout",
          "output_type": "stream",
          "text": [
            "Number of 3-mers: 64 (4^3 = 64)\n",
            "\n",
            "First 10 3-mers: ['AAA', 'AAC', 'AAG', 'AAT', 'ACA', 'ACC', 'ACG', 'ACT', 'AGA', 'AGC']\n"
          ]
        }
      ],
      "source": [
        "# Create a larger KmerPool\n",
        "trimers = KmerPool(length=3, alphabet='ACGT')\n",
        "print(f\"Number of 3-mers: {trimers.num_states} (4^3 = 64)\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# Generate all of them\n",
        "all_trimers = generate_seqs(trimers, combinatorially_complete_pools=[trimers], num_complete_iterations=1)\n",
        "print(f\"\\nFirst 10 3-mers: {all_trimers[:10]}\")\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## 3. ListPool: Choose from a List\n",
        "\n",
        "`ListPool` selects sequences from a provided list. It has a **finite** number of states equal to the length of the list.\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": 7,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [
        {
          "name": "stdout",
          "output_type": "stream",
          "text": [
            "ListPool: ATCG\n",
            "Number of states: 3\n",
            "\n",
            "All primers: ['ATCG', 'GCTA', 'TTAA']\n"
          ]
        }
      ],
      "source": [
        "# Create a ListPool\n",
        "primers = ListPool(['ATCG', 'GCTA', 'TTAA'])\n",
        "print(f\"ListPool: {primers}\")\n",
        "print(f\"Number of states: {primers.num_states}\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# Generate all sequences\n",
        "all_primers = generate_seqs(primers, combinatorially_complete_pools=[primers], num_complete_iterations=1)\n",
        "print(f\"\\nAll primers: {all_primers}\")\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "### Combinatorial Generation\n",
        "\n",
        "When you combine multiple pools, the total number of states is the **product** of individual states:\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": 8,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [
        {
          "name": "stdout",
          "output_type": "stream",
          "text": [
            "Combined pool has 6 states (3 × 2 = 6)\n",
            "Number of unique ancestors: 2\n",
            "\n",
            "All 6 sequences: ['A-X', 'A-Y', 'B-X', 'B-Y', 'C-X', 'C-Y']\n"
          ]
        }
      ],
      "source": [
        "# Combine two ListPools\n",
        "prefixes = ListPool(['A', 'B', 'C'])\n",
        "suffixes = ListPool(['X', 'Y'])\n",
        "combined = prefixes + '-' + suffixes\n",
        "\n",
        "print(f\"Combined pool has {combined.num_states} states (3 × 2 = 6)\")\n",
        "print(f\"Number of unique ancestors: {len(combined.ancestors)}\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# Generate all combinations\n",
        "all_sequences = generate_seqs(combined, combinatorially_complete_pools=[prefixes, suffixes], num_complete_iterations=1)\n",
        "print(f\"\\nAll {len(all_sequences)} sequences: {all_sequences}\")\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "### Reusing Pools\n",
        "\n",
        "An important feature: when the same pool is reused multiple times, it's counted only **once** in the state space:\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": 9,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [
        {
          "name": "stdout",
          "output_type": "stream",
          "text": [
            "Number of states: 3 (not 3³ = 27!)\n",
            "Unique ancestors: 1\n",
            "\n",
            "All 3 sequences: ['X-X-X', 'Y-Y-Y', 'Z-Z-Z']\n"
          ]
        }
      ],
      "source": [
        "# Reuse the same pool multiple times\n",
        "barcode = ListPool(['X', 'Y', 'Z'])\n",
        "repeated_use = barcode + '-' + barcode + '-' + barcode\n",
        "\n",
        "print(f\"Number of states: {repeated_use.num_states} (not 3³ = 27!)\")\n",
        "print(f\"Unique ancestors: {len(repeated_use.ancestors)}\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# When the same pool is reused, it has the same value in all positions\n",
        "sequences = generate_seqs(repeated_use, combinatorially_complete_pools=[barcode], num_complete_iterations=1)\n",
        "print(f\"\\nAll {len(sequences)} sequences: {sequences}\")\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## 4. RandomMutationPool: Random Mutations\n",
        "\n",
        "`RandomMutationPool` generates randomly mutated versions of an input sequence. Each position independently has a specified probability of being mutated to a different character from the alphabet.\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": 10,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [
        {
          "name": "stdout",
          "output_type": "stream",
          "text": [
            "Original sequence: ACGTACGT\n",
            "Number of states: inf (infinite)\n",
            "\n",
            "Generated sequences:\n",
            "  State 0: ACGGACGT\n",
            "  State 1: CGGTAGCT\n",
            "  State 2: ACATTCAT\n",
            "  State 3: TTGTACGT\n",
            "  State 4: CCGAACGT\n"
          ]
        }
      ],
      "source": [
        "# Basic usage with uniform mutation rate\n",
        "original_seq = 'ACGTACGT'\n",
        "mutator = RandomMutationPool(\n",
        "    seq=original_seq, \n",
        "    alphabet=['A', 'C', 'G', 'T'], \n",
        "    mutation_rate=0.3  # 30% chance of mutation at each position\n",
        ")\n",
        "\n",
        "print(f\"Original sequence: {original_seq}\")\n",
        "print(f\"Number of states: {mutator.num_states} (infinite)\")\n",
        "print(\"\\nGenerated sequences:\")\n",
        "for i in range(5):\n",
        "    mutator.set_state(i)\n",
        "    print(f\"  State {i}: {mutator.seq}\")\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "### Position-Specific Mutation Rates\n",
        "\n",
        "You can specify different mutation rates for each position by passing a list:\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": 11,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [
        {
          "name": "stdout",
          "output_type": "stream",
          "text": [
            "Original sequence: AAAA\n",
            "Mutation rates:    [0.0, 0.25, 0.75, 1.0]\n",
            "\n",
            "Generated sequences:\n",
            "  State 0: AAGG\n",
            "             ** (changed positions)\n",
            "  State 1: AAAG\n",
            "              * (changed positions)\n",
            "  State 2: AACC\n",
            "             ** (changed positions)\n",
            "  State 3: AATT\n",
            "             ** (changed positions)\n",
            "  State 4: AGCG\n",
            "            *** (changed positions)\n"
          ]
        }
      ],
      "source": [
        "# Position-specific mutation rates\n",
        "original = 'AAAA'\n",
        "rates = [0.0, 0.25, 0.75, 1.0]  # Different rate for each position\n",
        "\n",
        "mutator = RandomMutationPool(original, alphabet=['A', 'C', 'G', 'T'], mutation_rate=rates)\n",
        "\n",
        "print(f\"Original sequence: {original}\")\n",
        "print(f\"Mutation rates:    {rates}\")\n",
        "print(\"\\nGenerated sequences:\")\n",
        "for i in range(5):\n",
        "    mutator.set_state(i)\n",
        "    seq = mutator.seq\n",
        "    print(f\"  State {i}: {seq}\")\n",
        "    # Show which positions changed\n",
        "    changes = ['*' if seq[j] != original[j] else ' ' for j in range(len(seq))]\n",
        "    print(f\"           {''.join(changes)} (changed positions)\")\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "### Composition with Other Pools\n",
        "\n",
        "`RandomMutationPool` can be combined with other pool types:\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": 12,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [
        {
          "name": "stdout",
          "output_type": "stream",
          "text": [
            "Construct: fixed_prefix + mutated_core + fixed_suffix\n",
            "Total length: 12\n",
            "\n",
            "Generated sequences:\n",
            "  State 0: ATG NNNTNN TAA\n",
            "  State 1: ATG NNNTNN TAA\n",
            "  State 2: ATG NNNTNN TAA\n",
            "  State 3: ATG NNNTNN TAA\n",
            "  State 4: ATG NNNTNN TAA\n"
          ]
        }
      ],
      "source": [
        "# Create a construct with fixed flanking regions and mutated core\n",
        "prefix = Pool('ATG')  # Start codon\n",
        "core = RandomMutationPool('NNNNNN', alphabet=['A', 'C', 'G', 'T'], mutation_rate=0.4)\n",
        "suffix = Pool('TAA')  # Stop codon\n",
        "\n",
        "construct = prefix + core + suffix\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"Construct: fixed_prefix + mutated_core + fixed_suffix\")\n",
        "print(f\"Total length: {len(construct)}\")\n",
        "print(\"\\nGenerated sequences:\")\n",
        "for i in range(5):\n",
        "    construct.set_state(i)\n",
        "    seq = construct.seq\n",
        "    print(f\"  State {i}: {seq[:3]} {seq[3:9]} {seq[9:]}\")\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## 5. KMutationPool: Exactly K Mutations\n",
        "\n",
        "`KMutationPool` generates sequences with exactly k mutations. Unlike `RandomMutationPool` which has a probability of mutation at each position, `KMutationPool` guarantees exactly k positions will be mutated.\n",
        "\n",
        "### Key Features:\n",
        "- **Exact count**: Always produces exactly k mutations\n",
        "- **Non-adjacent mode** (default): Randomly selects k positions to mutate\n",
        "- **Adjacent mode**: Mutates k consecutive positions\n",
        "- Mutations always use a different character than the original\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": 13,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [
        {
          "name": "stdout",
          "output_type": "stream",
          "text": [
            "Original sequence: AAAAAAAA\n",
            "\n",
            "Generated sequences (k=2 mutations):\n",
            "  State 0: CCAAAAAA (mutations: 2)\n",
            "  State 1: CGAAAAAA (mutations: 2)\n",
            "  State 2: CTAAAAAA (mutations: 2)\n",
            "  State 3: GCAAAAAA (mutations: 2)\n",
            "  State 4: GGAAAAAA (mutations: 2)\n"
          ]
        }
      ],
      "source": [
        "# Basic usage: exactly 2 mutations (non-adjacent)\n",
        "original_seq = 'AAAAAAAA'\n",
        "k_mutator = KMutationPool(\n",
        "    seq=original_seq,\n",
        "    alphabet=['A', 'C', 'G', 'T'],\n",
        "    k=2  # Exactly 2 mutations\n",
        ")\n",
        "\n",
        "print(f\"Original sequence: {original_seq}\")\n",
        "print(\"\\nGenerated sequences (k=2 mutations):\")\n",
        "for i in range(5):\n",
        "    k_mutator.set_state(i)\n",
        "    seq = k_mutator.seq\n",
        "    # Count mutations\n",
        "    mutations = sum(1 for j in range(len(seq)) if seq[j] != original_seq[j])\n",
        "    print(f\"  State {i}: {seq} (mutations: {mutations})\")\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "### Adjacent Mutations\n",
        "\n",
        "With `adjacent=True`, `KMutationPool` mutates k consecutive positions:\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": 14,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [
        {
          "name": "stdout",
          "output_type": "stream",
          "text": [
            "Adjacent mode: 3 consecutive mutations\n",
            "Original: AAAAAAAA\n",
            "\n",
            "Generated sequences:\n",
            "  State 0: CCCAAAAA (positions [0, 1, 2])\n",
            "  State 1: CCGAAAAA (positions [0, 1, 2])\n",
            "  State 2: CCTAAAAA (positions [0, 1, 2])\n",
            "  State 3: CGCAAAAA (positions [0, 1, 2])\n",
            "  State 4: CGGAAAAA (positions [0, 1, 2])\n"
          ]
        }
      ],
      "source": [
        "# Adjacent mode: k consecutive mutations\n",
        "adjacent_mutator = KMutationPool(\n",
        "    seq='AAAAAAAA',\n",
        "    alphabet=['A', 'C', 'G', 'T'],\n",
        "    k=3,\n",
        "    adjacent=True  # Mutate 3 consecutive positions\n",
        ")\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"Adjacent mode: 3 consecutive mutations\")\n",
        "print(f\"Original: {'AAAAAAAA'}\")\n",
        "print(\"\\nGenerated sequences:\")\n",
        "for i in range(5):\n",
        "    adjacent_mutator.set_state(i)\n",
        "    seq = adjacent_mutator.seq\n",
        "    # Find mutated positions\n",
        "    mut_pos = [j for j in range(len(seq)) if seq[j] != 'A']\n",
        "    print(f\"  State {i}: {seq} (positions {mut_pos})\")\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "### Composition with Other Pools\n",
        "\n",
        "`KMutationPool` can be combined with other pool types to create complex constructs:\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": 15,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [
        {
          "name": "stdout",
          "output_type": "stream",
          "text": [
            "Construct: PREFIX- + [4-mer with 2 mutations] + -SUFFIX\n",
            "\n",
            "Generated sequences:\n",
            "  State 0: PREFIX-CCAA-SUFFIX\n",
            "  State 1: PREFIX-CCAC-SUFFIX\n",
            "  State 2: PREFIX-CCAG-SUFFIX\n",
            "  State 3: PREFIX-CCAT-SUFFIX\n",
            "  State 4: PREFIX-CCCA-SUFFIX\n"
          ]
        }
      ],
      "source": [
        "# Start with a 4-mer\n",
        "kmer = KmerPool(4, alphabet='ACGT')\n",
        "# Add exactly 2 mutations to it\n",
        "mutated_kmer = KMutationPool(kmer, alphabet=['A', 'C', 'G', 'T'], k=2)\n",
        "# Add flanking sequences\n",
        "construct = Pool('PREFIX-') + mutated_kmer + Pool('-SUFFIX')\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"Construct: PREFIX- + [4-mer with 2 mutations] + -SUFFIX\")\n",
        "print(\"\\nGenerated sequences:\")\n",
        "for i in range(5):\n",
        "    construct.set_state(i)\n",
        "    seq = construct.seq\n",
        "    print(f\"  State {i}: {seq}\")\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## 6. ShuffledPool: Sequence Permutations\n",
        "\n",
        "`ShuffledPool` generates permutations of an input sequence. Each permutation preserves the character composition but changes their order.\n",
        "\n",
        "### Key Features:\n",
        "- **Finite states**: Has L! states where L = len(seq)\n",
        "- **Sequential mode**: When L! ≤ max_num_states, systematically iterates through all permutations\n",
        "- **Random mode**: When L! > max_num_states, generates random shuffles to avoid memory issues\n",
        "- **Preserves composition**: Same characters, different order\n",
        "- **Deterministic with state**: Same state always produces the same permutation\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": 16,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [
        {
          "name": "stdout",
          "output_type": "stream",
          "text": [
