    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## 7. SubseqPool: Extract Subsequences\n",
        "\n",
        "The `SubseqPool` class extracts subsequences from a sequence with configurable tiling parameters. It's perfect for:\n",
        "- **Sliding windows**: Extract overlapping subsequences\n",
        "- **Non-overlapping tiles**: Divide a sequence into chunks\n",
        "- **Motif extraction**: Sample subsequences at specific intervals\n",
        "\n",
        "### Key Parameters\n",
        "\n",
        "- `seq`: The sequence to tile (string or Pool)\n",
        "- `width`: Width of each subsequence\n",
        "- `shift`: Number of positions to shift between adjacent subsequences\n",
        "- `offset`: Starting position (modulo width)"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": 23,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [
        {
          "name": "stdout",
          "output_type": "stream",
          "text": [
            "Original sequence: ACGTACGTACGT\n",
            "Width: 4, Shift: 2, Offset: 0\n",
            "Number of states: 5\n",
            "Is finite: True\n"
          ]
        }
      ],
      "source": [
        "# Create a SubseqPool\n",
        "seq = 'ACGTACGTACGT'\n",
        "pool = SubseqPool(seq, width=4, shift=2, offset=0)\n",
        "\n",
        "print(f\"Original sequence: {seq}\")\n",
        "print(f\"Width: 4, Shift: 2, Offset: 0\")\n",
        "print(f\"Number of states: {pool.num_states}\")\n",
        "print(f\"Is finite: {pool.is_sequential_compatible()}\")"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "### How num_states is Calculated\n",
        "\n",
        "The number of states is computed using the formula:\n",
        "\n",
        "```\n",
        "num_states = (L - O - W + S) // S\n",
        "```\n",
        "\n",
        "Where:\n",
        "- `L` = length of the sequence\n",
        "- `W` = width (subsequence length)\n",
        "- `S` = shift (step size)\n",
        "- `O` = offset % width (effective starting position)"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": 24,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [
        {
          "name": "stdout",
          "output_type": "stream",
          "text": [
            "Manual calculation: (12 - 0 - 4 + 2) // 2 = 5\n",
            "Pool num_states: 5\n",
            "✓ Formula verified!\n"
          ]
        }
      ],
      "source": [
        "# Verify the formula\n",
        "L = len(seq)  # 12\n",
        "W = 4\n",
        "S = 2\n",
        "O = 0\n",
        "\n",
        "calculated = (L - O - W + S) // S\n",
        "print(f\"Manual calculation: ({L} - {O} - {W} + {S}) // {S} = {calculated}\")\n",
        "print(f\"Pool num_states: {pool.num_states}\")\n",
        "print(f\"✓ Formula verified!\" if calculated == pool.num_states else \"✗ Mismatch!\")"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "### Sequential Iteration: Sliding Window\n",
        "\n",
        "When iterating sequentially through states, SubseqPool acts as a sliding window:"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": 25,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [
        {
          "name": "stdout",
          "output_type": "stream",
          "text": [
            "All subsequences with width=4, shift=2:\n",
            "Sequence: ACGTACGTACGT\n",
            "\n",
            "  State 0 (pos  0): ACGT\n",
            "  State 1 (pos  2): GTAC\n",
            "  State 2 (pos  4): ACGT\n",
            "  State 3 (pos  6): GTAC\n",
            "  State 4 (pos  8): ACGT\n"
          ]
        }
      ],
      "source": [
        "# Iterate through all subsequences\n",
        "print(f\"All subsequences with width=4, shift=2:\")\n",
        "print(f\"Sequence: {seq}\")\n",
        "print()\n",
        "\n",
        "for state in range(pool.num_states):\n",
        "    pool.set_state(state)\n",
        "    position = (0 + state * 2)  # offset + (state * shift)\n",
        "    print(f\"  State {state} (pos {position:2d}): {pool.seq}\")"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "### Composition with Other Pools\n",
        "\n",
        "SubseqPool can be combined with other pool types to create complex constructs:"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": 26,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [
        {
          "name": "stdout",
          "output_type": "stream",
          "text": [
            "Construct: 2 prefixes × 3 subsequences\n",
            "Total states: 6\n",
            "\n",
            "  State 0: X-AAATTT\n",
            "  State 1: X-TTTGGG\n",
            "  State 2: X-GGGCCC\n",
            "  State 3: Y-AAATTT\n",
            "  State 4: Y-TTTGGG\n",
            "  State 5: Y-GGGCCC\n"
          ]
        }
      ],
      "source": [
        "# Combine SubseqPool with ListPool\n",
        "template = 'AAATTTGGGCCC'\n",
        "subseq = SubseqPool(template, width=6, shift=3, offset=0)\n",
        "prefix = ListPool(['X-', 'Y-'])\n",
        "\n",
        "construct = prefix + subseq\n",
        "\n",
        "print(f\"Construct: {prefix.num_states} prefixes × {subseq.num_states} subsequences\")\n",
        "print(f\"Total states: {construct.num_states}\\n\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# Generate all combinations\n",
        "for state in range(construct.num_states):\n",
        "    construct.set_state(state)\n",
        "    print(f\"  State {state}: {construct.seq}\")\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "### Use Case: Motif Extraction\n",
        "\n",
        "SubseqPool is useful for extracting specific regions from sequences, such as extracting potential motifs or analyzing specific windows:\n"
