      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## 8. The generate_seqs() Function\n",
        "\n",
        "The `generate_seqs()` function supports flexible generation modes:\n",
        "- **Random mode**: Generate random sequences from pools\n",
        "- **Combinatorially complete mode**: Iterate through specific pools completely while randomizing others\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "### Random Generation\n",
        "\n",
        "Use `num_seqs` to generate a specific number of random sequences:\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": 28,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [
        {
          "name": "stdout",
          "output_type": "stream",
          "text": [
            "10 random sequences:\n",
            "  1. A-TAT\n",
            "  2. B-GGT\n",
            "  3. A-CTG\n",
            "  4. C-TTT\n",
            "  5. C-CTA\n",
            "  6. C-GCC\n",
            "  7. C-CAT\n",
            "  8. A-ACT\n",
            "  9. A-AGC\n",
            "  10. A-GCA\n"
          ]
        }
      ],
      "source": [
        "# Create a pool\n",
        "pool = ListPool(['A', 'B', 'C']) + '-' + KmerPool(length=3, alphabet='ACGT')\n",
        "\n",
        "# Generate 10 random sequences\n",
        "random_seqs = generate_seqs(pool, num_seqs=10)\n",
        "print(\"10 random sequences:\")\n",
        "for i, seq in enumerate(random_seqs, 1):\n",
        "    print(f\"  {i}. {seq}\")\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "### Partial Combinatorial Completion\n",
        "\n",
        "Use `combinatorially_complete_pools` to specify which pools should be iterated completely:\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": 29,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [
        {
          "name": "stdout",
          "output_type": "stream",
          "text": [
            "Pool structure: 2 × 4 × 3 = 24 total states\n",
            "\n",
            "With prefix complete, middle and suffix random (2 iterations):\n",
            "  1. A-YY-2\n",
            "  2. B-XY-1\n",
            "  3. A-XX-1\n",
            "  4. B-XY-1\n",
            "\n",
            "Total sequences: 4 (2 prefix states × 2 iterations = 4)\n"
          ]
        }
      ],
      "source": [
        "# Create pools\n",
        "prefix = ListPool(['A', 'B'])\n",
        "middle = KmerPool(length=2, alphabet='XY')\n",
        "suffix = ListPool(['1', '2', '3'])\n",
        "\n",
        "combined = prefix + '-' + middle + '-' + suffix\n",
        "\n",
        "print(f\"Pool structure: {prefix.num_states} × {middle.num_states} × {suffix.num_states} = {combined.num_states} total states\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# Generate with only prefix complete (middle and suffix random)\n",
        "print(\"\\nWith prefix complete, middle and suffix random (2 iterations):\")\n",
        "seqs = generate_seqs(combined, \n",
        "                    combinatorially_complete_pools=[prefix],\n",
        "                    num_complete_iterations=2)\n",
        "for i, seq in enumerate(seqs, 1):\n",
        "    print(f\"  {i}. {seq}\")\n",
        "\n",
        "print(f\"\\nTotal sequences: {len(seqs)} (2 prefix states × 2 iterations = 4)\")\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": 30,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [
        {
          "name": "stdout",
          "output_type": "stream",
          "text": [
            "With prefix and suffix complete, middle random (1 iteration):\n",
            "  1. A-YY-1\n",
            "  2. A-XY-2\n",
            "  3. A-XX-3\n",
            "  4. B-XY-1\n",
            "  5. B-XY-2\n",
            "  6. B-YX-3\n",
            "\n",
            "Total sequences: 6 (2 × 3 × 1 = 6)\n"
          ]
        }
      ],
      "source": [
        "# Generate with prefix and suffix complete (middle random)\n",
        "print(\"With prefix and suffix complete, middle random (1 iteration):\")\n",
        "seqs = generate_seqs(combined,\n",
        "                    combinatorially_complete_pools=[prefix, suffix],\n",
        "                    num_complete_iterations=1)\n",
        "for i, seq in enumerate(seqs, 1):\n",
        "    print(f\"  {i}. {seq}\")\n",
        "\n",
        "print(f\"\\nTotal sequences: {len(seqs)} (2 × 3 × 1 = 6)\")\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "### Full Combinatorial Completion\n",
