        "## 9. Summary\n",
        "\n",
        "The refactored poolparty architecture provides:\n",
        "\n",
        "**Unified Pool Classes:**\n",
        "- `KmerPool`: All k-mers from an alphabet (finite states)\n",
        "- `ListPool`: Choose from a list (finite states)\n",
        "- `ShuffledPool`: Random shuffles (infinite states)\n",
        "- `RandomMutationPool`: Random mutations at specified rates (infinite states)\n",
        "- `KMutationPool`: Exactly k mutations (finite states)\n",
        "- `SubseqPool`: Extract subsequences with tiling parameters (finite states)\n",
        "\n",
        "**Flexible Generation with generate_seqs():**\n",
        "- Random mode: `generate_seqs(pool, num_seqs=N)`\n",
        "- Complete mode: `generate_seqs(pool, combinatorially_complete_pools=[pool], num_complete_iterations=1)`\n",
        "- Mixed mode: `generate_seqs(pool, combinatorially_complete_pools=[pool1, pool2], num_complete_iterations=N)`\n",
        "\n",
        "**Key Features:**\n",
        "- All basic pools are finite\n",
        "- Seed support for reproducibility\n",
        "- Flexible control over which pools iterate completely vs randomly\n",
        "- Computation graphs for complex sequence design\n",
        "\n",
        "Happy pooling! 🎉\n"
